Extract the smoky richness from the bacon by baking it in the oven until crisp. Preheat the oven to 400ºF/200ºC. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/26/1909190-1a.jpg/460px-1909190-1a.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/26/1909190-1a.jpg/728px-1909190-1a.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"484","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Lay the bacon on an ungreased baking sheet (consider using a baking sheet that has turned up edges, which will prevent the bacon from sliding off the sheet and into the oven). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/1909190-1b.jpg/460px-1909190-1b.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/f/f0/1909190-1b.jpg/728px-1909190-1b.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"484","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Coat the raw bacon with the light brown sugar. Only coat one side to avoid the sugar making contact with the baking sheet and scorching. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d9/1909190-1c.jpg/460px-1909190-1c.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/d9/1909190-1c.jpg/728px-1909190-1c.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"484","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Bake for 10-12 minutes––turn after baking for approximately six to eight minutes. Consider dragging the bacon through any run off brown sugar (which will most likely have become a syrup) as you turn it. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/71/1909190-1d.jpg/460px-1909190-1d.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/71/1909190-1d.jpg/728px-1909190-1d.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"484","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cool bacon on a wire rack and break into small pieces once fully cooled. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/ba/1909190-1e.jpg/460px-1909190-1e.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/ba/1909190-1e.jpg/728px-1909190-1e.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"484","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use a hand mixer or a standalone mixer for best results. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4f/1909190-3a.jpg/460px-1909190-3a.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/4/4f/1909190-3a.jpg/728px-1909190-3a.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"484","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Mix at low speed or use a whisk to combine until the sugars are dissolved into the milk. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a6/1909190-3b.jpg/460px-1909190-3b.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/a/a6/1909190-3b.jpg/728px-1909190-3b.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"484","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
